pageContext.claim: “In fiscal year 2018, ICE made more than 1,500 human trafficking arrests, with 97 percent of that for sex trafficking.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump has the number of arrests (1,588) right, but ICE says those arrests resulted in 538 convictions. While Trump made this statement in support of a border wall, many of the ICE news releases on sex trafficking indicate the victims came through legal ports of entry.
